  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and grate the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Add the <strong>grated onion</strong>,<strong> beef mince</strong>,<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> to a large bowl</p><p>Massage thoroughly, with clean hands, until fully combined, then divide the mixture into 10<span class=\"text-danger\"> [20]</span> and roll into meatballs</p><p>Tip: Massage the meat longer for more tender meatballs!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]<strong> </span>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 4 min, turning occasionally, until they are browned (they don't need to be fully cooked through yet!)</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve the<strong> chicken stock</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>meatballs</strong> to a plate</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat, add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir until a sandy paste forms (if your pan is looking dry add a small knob of butter)</p><p>Whisk the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong> into the flour</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until it has thickened slightly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1524.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
